Text.SourceString: Biology test coming up. Bleh.//Valentina's supposed to help me study, but she's probably distracted by her latest art project.
Text.LocalizedString: Biology test coming up. Bleh.//Valentina's supposed to help me study, but she's probably distracted by her latest art project.

Text.SourceString: What are you doing tomorrow? Can you help me study?
Text.LocalizedString: What are you doing tomorrow? Can you help me study?

Text.SourceString: We're planning a trip to the forest – me, Oliver, Zoe...and Dad, yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: We're planning a trip to the forest – me, Oliver, Zoe...and Dad, yeah.

Text.SourceString: We're all grown up now; I don't know why Dad still wants to tag along.
Text.LocalizedString: We're all grown up now; I don't know why Dad still wants to tag along.

Text.SourceString: Heard about the stray dogs near the school? I'm thinking, 'Archie to the rescue!' Gotta start my vet career somewhere.
Text.LocalizedString: Heard about the stray dogs near the school? I'm thinking, 'Archie to the rescue!' Gotta start my vet career somewhere.

Text.SourceString: I can drop the pups off at the shelter for Mark to take care of.//<portrait=happy>Mom doesn't want me bringing animals back home anymore. 'They pooped everywhere,' she said.
Text.LocalizedString: I can drop the pups off at the shelter for Mark to take care of.//<portrait=happy>Mom doesn't want me bringing animals back home anymore. 'They pooped everywhere,' she said.

Text.SourceString: Miss those epic snowball fights already. I say we bring them back.//Forget studying, let's show these snowflakes who's boss.
Text.LocalizedString: Miss those epic snowball fights already. I say we bring them back.//Forget studying, let's show these snowflakes who's boss.

Text.SourceString: A good snow day like this and nothing – no snowball fight, nothing. I say we bring them back. Forget studying, let's show these snowflakes who's boss.
Text.LocalizedString: A good snow day like this and nothing – no snowball fight, nothing. I say we bring them back. Forget studying, let's show these snowflakes who's boss.

Text.SourceString: We always thought the forest was full of monsters, but guess what? They were just monkeys.//<portrait=doubt>Paul said so.
Text.LocalizedString: We always thought the forest was full of monsters, but guess what? They were just monkeys.//<portrait=doubt>Paul said so.

Text.SourceString: Dad taught me everything I know about kites. He's the original master.//But I think I'm better at it now.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad taught me everything I know about kites. He's the original master.//But I think I'm better at it now.

Text.SourceString: Last weekend at the vineyard was epic. Mrs. Bree's pasta? Chef's kiss! And I got leftovers – score.
Text.LocalizedString: Last weekend at the vineyard was epic. Mrs. Bree's pasta? Chef's kiss! And I got leftovers – score.

Text.SourceString: My rock collection's gotta stay small – Mom's orders. But man, choosing is tough when every rock looks like a gem.
Text.LocalizedString: My rock collection's gotta stay small – Mom's orders. But man, choosing is tough when every rock looks like a gem.

Text.SourceString: When Mrs. Bree's over, it's blah-blah-blah grown-up talk. I'm outta there, off to chill with Taco or the ducks. Way more fun.
Text.LocalizedString: When Mrs. Bree's over, it's blah-blah-blah grown-up talk. I'm outta there, off to chill with Taco or the ducks. Way more fun.

Text.SourceString: One day, I'll be the coolest vet in town. Just wait, I'll have a TV show and everything.
Text.LocalizedString: One day, I'll be the coolest vet in town. Just wait, I'll have a TV show and everything.

Text.SourceString: Got my whole vet career planned out. First, ace biology, then college, then...hmm...//<portrait=doubt>Work for Mark?
Text.LocalizedString: Got my whole vet career planned out. First, ace biology, then college, then...hmm...//<portrait=doubt>Work for Mark?

Text.SourceString: Anyone up for a game after school? I promise I'll go easy on you...maybe.
Text.LocalizedString: Anyone up for a game after school? I promise I'll go easy on you...maybe.

Text.SourceString: Hey, let's all hit the Winter Fair together. The more of us, the more fun it'll be!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, let's all hit the Winter Fair together. The more of us, the more fun it'll be!

Text.SourceString: Dad's old camping stories are the best. Can't beat a classic.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad's old camping stories are the best. Can't beat a classic.

Text.SourceString: Mom's advice may be a bit old-school, but she's usually right. Don't tell her I said that.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom's advice may be a bit old-school, but she's usually right. Don't tell her I said that.

Text.SourceString: Family hikes are a tradition. Sure, they're cheesy, but I wouldn't miss them for anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Family hikes are a tradition. Sure, they're cheesy, but I wouldn't miss them for anything.

Text.SourceString: Mom's not a fan of my rock collection, but she still helps me clean them. She's cool like that.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom's not a fan of my rock collection, but she still helps me clean them. She's cool like that.

Text.SourceString: The forest is my second home. I love the smell of pine and adventure.
Text.LocalizedString: The forest is my second home. I love the smell of pine and adventure.

Text.SourceString: I tried to be serious once. Worst two minutes of my life.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to be serious once. Worst two minutes of my life.

Text.SourceString: I could make a joke about sodium, but Na, too easy.//My uncle told me that. Is it lame?
Text.LocalizedString: I could make a joke about sodium, but Na, too easy.//My uncle told me that. Is it lame?

Text.SourceString: I told some of my original jokes to Valentina. She's putting them into her big book of jokes. If we get rich from it, she's going to give me some <Italic>loyalty</>.//<portrait=happy>Yeah... Right, royalty.
Text.LocalizedString: I told some of my original jokes to Valentina. She's putting them into her big book of jokes. If we get rich from it, she's going to give me some <Italic>loyalty</>.//<portrait=happy>Yeah... Right, royalty.

Text.SourceString: Zoe and I are planning a hike at the forest this weekend. She really knows her way around the woods. It's...impressive.
Text.LocalizedString: Zoe and I are planning a hike at the forest this weekend. She really knows her way around the woods. It's...impressive.

Text.SourceString: I saw this rare bird while birdwatching. First person I thought to tell? Zoe. She'd totally get why it was so cool.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw this rare bird while birdwatching. First person I thought to tell? Zoe. She'd totally get why it was so cool.

Text.SourceString: I'm learning about different plant species – Zoe's into that stuff. Not gonna lie, it's actually pretty fascinating.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm learning about different plant species – Zoe's into that stuff. Not gonna lie, it's actually pretty fascinating.

Text.SourceString: Zoe beat me in climbing the old oak tree again. She's just so... I don't know, awesome?
Text.LocalizedString: Zoe beat me in climbing the old oak tree again. She's just so... I don't know, awesome?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, Valentina and Oliver are cool too.//<portrait=happy>Zoe's different though. Her hair smells kinda nice too.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, Valentina and Oliver are cool too.//<portrait=happy>Zoe's different though. Her hair smells kinda nice too.

Text.SourceString: We have this tradition where everyone shares their day at dinner. It's kinda nice, actually.//<portrait=happy>Makes even a boring day seem important.
Text.LocalizedString: We have this tradition where everyone shares their day at dinner. It's kinda nice, actually.//<portrait=happy>Makes even a boring day seem important.

Text.SourceString: What should I talk about today? Oh, and seeing you here definitely's going to be part of tonight's dinner table conversation.
Text.LocalizedString: What should I talk about today? Oh, and seeing you here definitely's going to be part of tonight's dinner table conversation.

Text.SourceString: Mom's pesto pasta is the best, hands down. She taught me how to make it from scratch – it's my all-time favorite food.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom's pesto pasta is the best, hands down. She taught me how to make it from scratch – it's my all-time favorite food.

Text.SourceString: Whenever there's a school potluck, I bring Mom's pesto pasta. It's always a hit, and everyone thinks she's some kind of pasta wizard.//Which she is!
Text.LocalizedString: Whenever there's a school potluck, I bring Mom's pesto pasta. It's always a hit, and everyone thinks she's some kind of pasta wizard.//Which she is!

Text.SourceString: Macy at the inn has this pet lobster named Stephen. Weird, right? I got to pet it once. It was so cool.//<portrait=happy>Where do you think I can get one of those?
Text.LocalizedString: Macy at the inn has this pet lobster named Stephen. Weird, right? I got to pet it once. It was so cool.//<portrait=happy>Where do you think I can get one of those?

Text.SourceString: 7 am wake-ups for school are brutal. Who decided that was a good idea?
Text.LocalizedString: 7 am wake-ups for school are brutal. Who decided that was a good idea?

Text.SourceString: Hmm... yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm... yeah?

Text.SourceString: Might hang out with Uncle Surya at the vineyard tomorrow. Or maybe fly kites with friends if they're up for it.
Text.LocalizedString: Might hang out with Uncle Surya at the vineyard tomorrow. Or maybe fly kites with friends if they're up for it.

Text.SourceString: What's your plan today? I'm stuck with school till tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: What's your plan today? I'm stuck with school till tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I love exploring the forest. Not the boring part near Ben's, but the real wild part. Ever wonder if there are bears or snakes out there?
Text.LocalizedString: I love exploring the forest. Not the boring part near Ben's, but the real wild part. Ever wonder if there are bears or snakes out there?

Text.SourceString: Oliver lent me his detective comics. They're alright.
Text.LocalizedString: Oliver lent me his detective comics. They're alright.

Text.SourceString: Art class was all about recycling water bottles. I get the point, but I'd rather learn about renewable energy or something.
Text.LocalizedString: Art class was all about recycling water bottles. I get the point, but I'd rather learn about renewable energy or something.

Text.SourceString: Whenever I see trash in the forest, I pick it up. It's not much, but it's about respecting the environment.//<portrait=happy>My uncle taught me that.
Text.LocalizedString: Whenever I see trash in the forest, I pick it up. It's not much, but it's about respecting the environment.//<portrait=happy>My uncle taught me that.

Text.SourceString: Favorite mushroom? No way, they're all gross.
Text.LocalizedString: Favorite mushroom? No way, they're all gross.

Text.SourceString: This one time, we caught a boatload of fish. Mom whipped up fish tacos for my entire class. They were a hit.
Text.LocalizedString: This one time, we caught a boatload of fish. Mom whipped up fish tacos for my entire class. They were a hit.

Text.SourceString: Mom and Dad bring home flowers, and Mom turns them into bouquets. She's got a thing for pretty stuff.//The house always looks nice.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom and Dad bring home flowers, and Mom turns them into bouquets. She's got a thing for pretty stuff.//The house always looks nice.

Text.SourceString: Hey.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey.

Text.SourceString: Dad told me to pick some flowers for Mom if I see any. She's been wanting to freshen up the house with some new ones.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad told me to pick some flowers for Mom if I see any. She's been wanting to freshen up the house with some new ones.

Text.SourceString: Ugh, rain ruins everything – no biking, no hanging out. Just stuck inside with wet shoes.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, rain ruins everything – no biking, no hanging out. Just stuck inside with wet shoes.

Text.SourceString: Sunny days are awesome.
Text.LocalizedString: Sunny days are awesome.

Text.SourceString: It's nice and warm today.
Text.LocalizedString: It's nice and warm today.

Text.SourceString: Storms freak me out, especially lightning. It's kinda scary, so I just stay inside.
Text.LocalizedString: Storms freak me out, especially lightning. It's kinda scary, so I just stay inside.

Text.SourceString: Summer barbecues are the best. Dad makes awesome burgers.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer barbecues are the best. Dad makes awesome burgers.

Text.SourceString: Now that it's Summer, I can play outside way more. It's awesome!
Text.LocalizedString: Now that it's Summer, I can play outside way more. It's awesome!

Text.SourceString: Spring cleaning's a family thing. Not fun, but we all have to help.//<portrait=annoyed>Valentina told me her mom does it too. And she's hardcore, <Italic>dude</>! Like, hardcore!!!
Text.LocalizedString: Spring cleaning's a family thing. Not fun, but we all have to help.//<portrait=annoyed>Valentina told me her mom does it too. And she's hardcore, <Italic>dude</>! Like, hardcore!!!

Text.SourceString: She told me that her mom makes her own cleaning supplies...yeah, I know!
Text.LocalizedString: She told me that her mom makes her own cleaning supplies...yeah, I know!

Text.SourceString: It's cool seeing everything get green in Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: It's cool seeing everything get green in Spring.

Text.SourceString: I helped Mom with her garden this Spring. It's actually kinda cool to see stuff grow.
Text.LocalizedString: I helped Mom with her garden this Spring. It's actually kinda cool to see stuff grow.

Text.SourceString: I start getting ready for Winter fair sports in the Fall. Gotta be ready for curling.
Text.LocalizedString: I start getting ready for Winter fair sports in the Fall. Gotta be ready for curling.

Text.SourceString: I've got my eye on this cool, fancy rock polisher, but Mom says the old one works fine. She's like, 'Get a job if you want a new one.'//<portrait=happy>So, do you need help at the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: I've got my eye on this cool, fancy rock polisher, but Mom says the old one works fine. She's like, 'Get a job if you want a new one.'//<portrait=happy>So, do you need help at the farm?

Text.SourceString: How much does it pay?
Text.LocalizedString: How much does it pay?

Text.SourceString: I'm helping out at the shop with my uncles this Summer. No pay, though - Dad's too cheap.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha! Nah. It's cool. It's my shop too, so it's sort of my duty to help when I can.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm helping out at the shop with my uncles this Summer. No pay, though - Dad's too cheap.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha! Nah. It's cool. It's my shop too, so it's sort of my duty to help when I can.

Text.SourceString: My Uncle Surya let me mess around with his lab gear once – it was epic
Text.LocalizedString: My Uncle Surya let me mess around with his lab gear once – it was epic

Text.SourceString: Crickets sleeping all day and then looking for food at night – that's kind of like my ideal life.
Text.LocalizedString: Crickets sleeping all day and then looking for food at night – that's kind of like my ideal life.

Text.SourceString: Gotta watch what I pick up in the forest – some of that stuff is seriously sketchy, not just gross but dangerous.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta watch what I pick up in the forest – some of that stuff is seriously sketchy, not just gross but dangerous.

Text.SourceString: We learned about planting dragon fruit in Winter at school. It's actually a cactus. Who knew cacti could be that cool?
Text.LocalizedString: We learned about planting dragon fruit in Winter at school. It's actually a cactus. Who knew cacti could be that cool?

Text.SourceString: Dragon fruit trees look like some mythical creature, all spiky and wild. My uncle's got a bunch. You should see them!
Text.LocalizedString: Dragon fruit trees look like some mythical creature, all spiky and wild. My uncle's got a bunch. You should see them!

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Dude</>, I'm so tired... I could go for a nap right now.
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Dude</>, I'm so tired... I could go for a nap right now.

Text.SourceString: Really hoping it doesn't storm tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Really hoping it doesn't storm tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Player, you're old. How do you make so much money?//I want to make enough to give my mom the biggest garden ever – she loves gardening.
Text.LocalizedString: Player, you're old. How do you make so much money?//I want to make enough to give my mom the biggest garden ever – she loves gardening.

Text.SourceString: Yes! It's snowing!
Text.LocalizedString: Yes! It's snowing!

Text.SourceString: Snowball fight time! Hope you're ready because I've been practicing my aim.
Text.LocalizedString: Snowball fight time! Hope you're ready because I've been practicing my aim.

Text.SourceString: Saw these awesome butterflies on my way to school today. Might sketch them for art class.
Text.LocalizedString: Saw these awesome butterflies on my way to school today. Might sketch them for art class.

Text.SourceString: I'm like hungry all the time now. The doctor says it's because I'm in a growing phase. Makes sense, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm like hungry all the time now. The doctor says it's because I'm in a growing phase. Makes sense, I guess.

Text.SourceString: I asked Kenny about helping out at the ranch, but he told me to stick with school for now. He says I can come by on weekends if I want.
Text.LocalizedString: I asked Kenny about helping out at the ranch, but he told me to stick with school for now. He says I can come by on weekends if I want.

Text.SourceString: He's right, school's important if I want to become a vet. Mr. Barnes said the same thing.
Text.LocalizedString: He's right, school's important if I want to become a vet. Mr. Barnes said the same thing.

Text.SourceString: Taco is the smartest dog I know. One time, I let him sniff my sock, and he actually helped me find the matching one I lost.//Your pet smart like that, Player?
Text.LocalizedString: Taco is the smartest dog I know. One time, I let him sniff my sock, and he actually helped me find the matching one I lost.//Your pet smart like that, Player?

Text.SourceString: Forgot my kite today. Perfect wind for it too. Oh well!
Text.LocalizedString: Forgot my kite today. Perfect wind for it too. Oh well!

Text.SourceString: Ugh, got the sniffles. <Italic>achoo</>! Must be this crazy weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, got the sniffles. <Italic>achoo</>! Must be this crazy weather.

Text.SourceString: *achoo!*
Text.LocalizedString: *achoo!*

Text.SourceString: Mom thinks I'll make a great vet since I love animals so much.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom thinks I'll make a great vet since I love animals so much.

Text.SourceString: Umm… No, thanks. I don’t want to be a farmer. I don’t like gardening that much.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm… No, thanks. I don’t want to be a farmer. I don’t like gardening that much.

Text.SourceString: I only get to go to the Winter Fair with my parents. They're worried I might get lost in the crowd.
Text.LocalizedString: I only get to go to the Winter Fair with my parents. They're worried I might get lost in the crowd.

Text.SourceString: We're learning music at school. Maybe I'll show off a bit at the next festival – let everyone hear my skills.
Text.LocalizedString: We're learning music at school. Maybe I'll show off a bit at the next festival – let everyone hear my skills.

Text.SourceString: Had a blast at the vineyard last weekend. Mrs. Bree's pasta is just...chef's kiss.
Text.LocalizedString: Had a blast at the vineyard last weekend. Mrs. Bree's pasta is just...chef's kiss.

Text.SourceString: I like going to the library.
Text.LocalizedString: I like going to the library.

Text.SourceString: Millie often lets us read the new books that aren't even on the shelves yet, the ones she's still sorting. She's pretty cool.
Text.LocalizedString: Millie often lets us read the new books that aren't even on the shelves yet, the ones she's still sorting. She's pretty cool.

Text.SourceString: Luke lets me play with Taco, but he's always like, 'Be careful with treats.' Got it, no chocolate or grapes for dogs.
Text.LocalizedString: Luke lets me play with Taco, but he's always like, 'Be careful with treats.' Got it, no chocolate or grapes for dogs.

Text.SourceString: Tomorrow is Friday, then the weekend! Yay!
Text.LocalizedString: Tomorrow is Friday, then the weekend! Yay!

Text.SourceString: I wonder what we’re gonna do tomorrow at school.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what we’re gonna do tomorrow at school.

Text.SourceString: What do farmers even do on Mondays? Is it like a super busy day for you?
Text.LocalizedString: What do farmers even do on Mondays? Is it like a super busy day for you?

Text.SourceString: I wish I could go to the forest today and look for bugs. Maybe tomorrow if Dad's not too busy.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could go to the forest today and look for bugs. Maybe tomorrow if Dad's not too busy.

Text.SourceString: It's always amazing to see my parents working on big projects, like those huge barns and coops for animals. Did you see the massive one at Jack's place? Yeah, my parents built that.
Text.LocalizedString: It's always amazing to see my parents working on big projects, like those huge barns and coops for animals. Did you see the massive one at Jack's place? Yeah, my parents built that.

Text.SourceString: Whenever Mom wants to make banana fritters, she sends Dad and me to the forest to pick bananas. Dad loves those fritters.
Text.LocalizedString: Whenever Mom wants to make banana fritters, she sends Dad and me to the forest to pick bananas. Dad loves those fritters.

Text.SourceString: Mom thinks the bananas from Sam’s store just don't match up to the ones we find in the forest. Plus, Dad says they're too pricey.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom thinks the bananas from Sam’s store just don't match up to the ones we find in the forest. Plus, Dad says they're too pricey.

Text.SourceString: I don't bring bugs home from the forest. The house rule is we only take home what we can eat. So, the bugs stay where they are.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't bring bugs home from the forest. The house rule is we only take home what we can eat. So, the bugs stay where they are.

Text.SourceString: I’m hungry… I want some snacks.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m hungry… I want some snacks.

Text.SourceString: Do you just walk around the island on the weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you just walk around the island on the weekend?

Text.SourceString: Valentina said that Macy got this incredible new video game. I'm thinking about going over to check it out.//But the inn is so far, not sure if I'm up for that long walk.
Text.LocalizedString: Valentina said that Macy got this incredible new video game. I'm thinking about going over to check it out.//But the inn is so far, not sure if I'm up for that long walk.

Text.SourceString: I added cool birds and bugs I saw to my journal. Can't wait to show everyone at school tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I added cool birds and bugs I saw to my journal. Can't wait to show everyone at school tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Left my reading notes at home. Guess I won't have much to say in class today.
Text.LocalizedString: Left my reading notes at home. Guess I won't have much to say in class today.

Text.SourceString: Do you want my lunch? I think I’ll get tacos today.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you want my lunch? I think I’ll get tacos today.

Text.SourceString: When I grow up, I want to explore forests around the world, see all the different animals.
Text.LocalizedString: When I grow up, I want to explore forests around the world, see all the different animals.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna go in and get some juice… <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> said I could take whatever I want from her fridge.//She’s so nice.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna go in and get some juice… <NPCName>Mrs. Bree</> said I could take whatever I want from her fridge.//She’s so nice.

Text.SourceString: I ate all my burrito… Now what?
Text.LocalizedString: I ate all my burrito… Now what?

Text.SourceString: Whoa, look at these comic books!
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa, look at these comic books!

Text.SourceString: Oh man! I forgot to wash the rocks I got last week.//Mom is gonna be mad when she goes in my room.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh man! I forgot to wash the rocks I got last week.//Mom is gonna be mad when she goes in my room.

Text.SourceString: Oh well… Too late. Can’t do anything now.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well… Too late. Can’t do anything now.

Text.SourceString: My favorite bug is crickets. I really like beetles too. Especially the ones with red dots.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite bug is crickets. I really like beetles too. Especially the ones with red dots.

Text.SourceString: I don’t have a favorite mushroom, because they all taste horrible.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t have a favorite mushroom, because they all taste horrible.

Text.SourceString: Aww, no… I wish I’d brought my box of rocks. I think they’d look nice and shiny here.
Text.LocalizedString: Aww, no… I wish I’d brought my box of rocks. I think they’d look nice and shiny here.

Text.SourceString: Hanging out outside is the best. And you know what's cool? You can even smell Emma's tacos from here. They're so good!
Text.LocalizedString: Hanging out outside is the best. And you know what's cool? You can even smell Emma's tacos from here. They're so good!

Text.SourceString: What to do next... Hmm, maybe I'll shoot some hoops. Basketball sounds fun right now.
Text.LocalizedString: What to do next... Hmm, maybe I'll shoot some hoops. Basketball sounds fun right now.

Text.SourceString: Mr. Barnes prefers teaching outside, except when it rains. Then we're stuck indoors all day.
Text.LocalizedString: Mr. Barnes prefers teaching outside, except when it rains. Then we're stuck indoors all day.

Text.SourceString: Forgot my jump rope today...again.//I'm thinking I'll ask Valentina if I can borrow hers.
Text.LocalizedString: Forgot my jump rope today...again.//I'm thinking I'll ask Valentina if I can borrow hers.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and sunny today, so our class is out here.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and sunny today, so our class is out here.

Text.SourceString: Mom and Dad do yoga here on the weekend.//I don’t wanna join in, because I don’t like yoga.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom and Dad do yoga here on the weekend.//I don’t wanna join in, because I don’t like yoga.

Text.SourceString: That community center over there? It's huge inside! Must've taken ages to build.
Text.LocalizedString: That community center over there? It's huge inside! Must've taken ages to build.

Text.SourceString: Vitamin D is good for you. You can get it by being outside.//It comes from the sun.
Text.LocalizedString: Vitamin D is good for you. You can get it by being outside.//It comes from the sun.

Text.SourceString: The animal shelter has so many black cats.//<portrait=happy>I like black cats! They’re so cool!
Text.LocalizedString: The animal shelter has so many black cats.//<portrait=happy>I like black cats! They’re so cool!

Text.SourceString: I want one!//Maybe two… I want all the animals.
Text.LocalizedString: I want one!//Maybe two… I want all the animals.

Text.SourceString: So, I thought now that I'm older, I'd start calling Uncle Surya by his first name, you know?//But the moment I tried, Mom shut it down real quick. She's like, 'None of that disrespectful stuff.'//I mean, he's technically my cousin, not really an uncle. More like a big cousin, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: So, I thought now that I'm older, I'd start calling Uncle Surya by his first name, you know?//But the moment I tried, Mom shut it down real quick. She's like, 'None of that disrespectful stuff.'//I mean, he's technically my cousin, not really an uncle. More like a big cousin, I guess.

Text.SourceString: But whatever, I'll stick to 'Uncle.' That's just how it is with family. They've got their own set of weird rules.
Text.LocalizedString: But whatever, I'll stick to 'Uncle.' That's just how it is with family. They've got their own set of weird rules.
